br>- Pears can be preserved: add <b>300 g water<b> in <b>step 1,<b> then in <b>step 2<b> place the cooked pears in sterilised jars and pour the hot spiced wine into the jars to cover the pears. Seal the jars immediately and turn upside down for <b>10 minutes.<b> Preserved pears can be stored refrigerated for a few weeks, and must be eaten within <b>7 days<b> of opening the jar.<br>- For a sweet-savoury combination, serve the pears in red wine with blue cheese, such as Gorgaonzola.","For a faster result, omit <b>step 2<b> and reduce the spiced wine immediately, without marinating the pears. In this case the pears will remain white.<br>- You can replace or add to the spices in the wine according to your preference (e.g. star anise, cardamom pods, vanilla)."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h 20m","6 portions"]}